{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K6S9FTWc4Mt7jLihK2J2QP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary report of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the backend settlement integration tests and the settle-tx implementation. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Integration Test Location & Setup**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n**Test Setup Pattern**:\n- Uses a **real Postgres database** (connects via `DATABASE_URL` or defaults to `postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`)\n- **MockConnection class** (lines 64–191) implements minimal `@solana/web3.js` Connection interface:\n  - In-memory account storage via `setAccount()` / `removeAccount()`\n  - Mocks: `getAccountInfo()`, `getProgramAccounts()`, `getSlot()`, `getLatestBlockhash()`, `sendRawTransaction()`, `confirmTransaction()`, `getBlockTime()`, `getBalance()`\n  - No real RPC calls — all state is deterministic\n- **Isolation**: `TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY` before each test\n- **JWT**: Uses `HS256` with static test secret (`\"test-secret-for-integration-tests\"`)\n- **Pre-population**: Entropy account + PlatformConfig account are set up in mock before each test\n\n### 2. **Fixture Setup for Settlement (lines 271–309)**\n\n```typescript\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  // Clean tables\n  await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`;\n  \n  // Fresh mock Connection\n  mockConn = new MockConnection();\n  \n  // Pre-populate entropy + config\n  mockConn.setAccount(entropyAccount, entropyData);\n  mockConn.setAccount(configPda, configAccountData, { owner: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID });\n  \n  // Build Hono app with routes\n  app = new Hono();\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({...}));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n});\n```\n\n### 3. **How SettleTxDeps is Passed (lines 399–413)**\n\nIn the test, `SettleTxDeps` is created inline when calling `settleMatch()`:\n\n```typescript\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) =>\n    settleMatch(\n      {\n        db,\n        connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n        serverKeypair,\n        entropyAccount,\n        referralDefaultRateBps: 1000,  // ← PASSED HERE as a number\n      },\n      pda,\n    ),\n});\n```\n\n### 4. **SettleTxDeps Interface** (settle-tx.ts, lines 58–64)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;  // ← Rate in basis points (1000 = 10%)\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **recordReferralEarnings Function** (lines 123–195)\n\nThis is called from **both** `settleMatch()` and `settleLordRound()` at the end of settlement:\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- **Signature** (lines 123–131):\n  ```typescript\n  async function recordReferralEarnings(\n    db: Db,\n    params: {\n      roundId: string;\n      gameType: string;\n      feeBps: number;\n      referralDefaultRateBps: number;  // ← Passed down from SettleTxDeps\n      players: Array<{ wallet: string; wagerLamports: number }>;\n    },\n  ): Promise<void>\n  ```\n\n- **Logic** (lines 141–194):\n  1. **Deduplicate players** (Lord of RNGs can have multiple entries per player)\n  2. **For each unique wallet**:\n     - Look up referral link via `db.getReferralLinkByReferee(wallet)`\n     - If no referrer exists, skip (continue)\n     - Get referrer's custom rate via `db.getReferrerRate(referrerWallet, referralDefaultRateBps)`\n     - **Calculate earnings**:\n       - Fee: `(wager × feeBps) / 10_000`\n       - Referrer earned: `(fee × referrerRateBps) / 10_000`\n       - Referee rebate: `(fee × 1000) / 10_000` (fixed 10% v1)\n     - **Insert via DB** using `db.insertReferralEarning({})`\n     - **Idempotency**: UNIQUE constraint on (referee_wallet, round_id) prevents duplicate records on retry\n\n- **Error Handling** (lines 179–193):\n  - Catches duplicate key errors → logs as \"already recorded (idempotent skip)\"\n  - Other errors → logged but NOT rethrown (settlement must not fail due to referral recording)\n\n### 6. **Call Sites in Settlement Functions**\n\n**In `settleMatch()` (lines 382–391)**:\n```typescript\n// Referral earnings hook — in same transaction for atomicity (System Invariant 4)\nawait recordReferralEarnings(txDb, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  gameType: \"coinflip\",\n  feeBps,\n  referralDefaultRateBps: deps.referralDefaultRateBps,\n  players: [\n    { wallet: creator.toBase58(), wagerLamports: Number(entryAmount) },\n    { wallet: opponent.toBase58(), wagerLamports: Number(entryAmount) },\n  ],\n});\n```\n\n**In `settleLordRound()` (lines 595–604)**:\n```typescript\n// Referral earnings hook — in same transaction for atomicity (System Invariant 4)\nawait recordReferralEarnings(txDb, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  gameType: \"lord\",\n  feeBps,\n  referralDefaultRateBps: deps.referralDefaultRateBps,\n  players: serializedEntries.map((e) => ({\n    wallet: e.player,\n    wagerLamports: e.amountLamports,\n  })),\n});\n```\n\n### 7. **Production Instantiation** (index.ts, line 124)\n\nThe `referralDefaultRateBps` comes from the config:\n\n```typescript\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) =>\n    settleRound(\n      { \n        db, \n        connection, \n        serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, \n        entropyAccount, \n        referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps  // ← From env\n      },\n      pda,\n    ),\n});\n```\n\n**Config source** (config.ts, lines 95–97):\n```typescript\nreferralDefaultRateBps: parseInt(\n  process.env.REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS ?? \"1000\",  // Default 10%\n  10,\n),\n```\n\n### 8. **DB Fixtures in Other Tests**\n\nThe **referral-routes.test.ts** file (lines 1–782) shows additional test patterns for referral operations:\n- Uses the same DB isolation pattern (TRUNCATE in beforeEach)\n- Directly inserts test data via `db.insertReferralEarning()` (lines 427–438)\n- Tests referral stats, earnings pagination, claim flow\n- Shows actual referral earning structure with `referrerRateBps`, `refereeRebateLamports`, etc.\n\n### 9. **Mocking Patterns Summary**\n\n| Component | Mock/Real | Implementation |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **Connection** | Mock | In-memory account storage + deterministic RPC |\n| **Database** | Real | Connects to actual Postgres instance |\n| **JWT** | Mocked | Static secret, fixed TTL |\n| **Entropy** | Mock | Pre-set buffer in MockConnection |\n| **Config** | Test setup | Hardcoded test values (amounts, sides, slots) |\n| **Chain state** | Mock | All accounts pre-populated before test |\n\n### 10. **File Paths (Absolute)**\n\n- **Main test file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n- **Source under test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n- **Settlement worker**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n- **Retry settler**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/retry.ts`\n- **Config loader**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n- **Main index**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n- **Referral test helper**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/referral-routes.test.ts`\n\nThis structure ensures that `referralDefaultRateBps` flows through the entire settlement pipeline atomically and is passed down from the config layer through the retry settler into both `settleMatch()` and `settleLordRound()`, where it's used in the `recordReferralEarnings()` function to calculate referrer payouts."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9e5154364afa435e (use SendMessage with to: 'a9e5154364afa435e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 84163\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 80507</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"773e2b1e-9c3d-4d53-809d-a95c06988ae7","uuid":"c7fca564-a863-4ce2-b546-10cae4d82be1","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:56:48.553Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the existing backend integration tests for settlement (settle-tx). I need to understand:\n1. Where the settle-tx integration tests live\n2. How they set up test fixtures (DB, deps, etc.)\n3. What patterns they use for mocking RPC/connection\n4. The SettleTxDeps interface and how referralDefaultRateBps is passed\n\nSearch in sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/ for settle-tx test files and the settle-tx.ts source. Read the full test file and relevant parts of settle-tx.ts (especially the recordReferralEarnings function and how it's called from settleMatch/settleLordRound).\n\nThoroughness: very thorough","agentId":"a9e5154364afa435e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary report of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the backend settlement integration tests and the settle-tx implementation. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Integration Test Location & Setup**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n**Test Setup Pattern**:\n- Uses a **real Postgres database** (connects via `DATABASE_URL` or defaults to `postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`)\n- **MockConnection class** (lines 64–191) implements minimal `@solana/web3.js` Connection interface:\n  - In-memory account storage via `setAccount()` / `removeAccount()`\n  - 