{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019USxS5ntUHutfN9GVCkxmC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete understanding of the integration test pattern. I need to add a new test that:\n\n1. Creates a coinflip game\n2. Sets up referral links in the DB (referrer → opponent as referee)\n3. Simulates joining (mock locked match account)\n4. Settles the match\n5. Verifies `referral_earnings` rows exist with correct amounts\n\nLet me also check if there's a KOL rate test I should include.\n\nThe key calculations:\n- wager = 5,000,000 lamports\n- fee = wager * 500 / 10000 = 250,000 lamports\n\n\n- referrer_earned = fee * 1000 / 10000 = 25,000 lamports\n- referee_rebate = fee * 1000 / 10000 = 25,000 lamports\n\nI'll add a new test to the existing integration.test.ts file that creates a referral code for the referrer wallet, establishes the referral link between referrer and opponent, runs the settlement, and then verifies the referral_earnings table has the correct entries. I need to make sure the beforeEach includes referral table cleanup and add the new test case.\n\nWriting the test setup and assertions...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1455,"cache_read_input_tokens":65864,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1455},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"773e2b1e-9c3d-4d53-809d-a95c06988ae7","uuid":"45df4215-085d-4afb-9802-7cdda592ed2c"}
